<title>USA: Clarify adopts shareholder rights plan.</title>
<headline>Clarify adopts shareholder rights plan.</headline>
<dateline>SAN JOSE, Calif. 1997-06-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>Clarify Inc said it adopted a shareholder rights plan in which preferred stock purchase rights will be distributed as a dividend at the rate of one right for each common share held as of the close of business June 30.</p>
<p>The rights will be exercisable only if a person or group, other than an exempted person, makes a tender offer for, or acquires beneficial ownership of 15 percent or more of the company's common stock, Clarify said in a news release.</p>
<p>The statement did not say whether the company was being targeted for takeover and company officials could not be reached Sunday.</p>
<p>The rights plan is effective immediately and expires on June 13, 2007, Clarify said.</p>
